    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>NAME</title>
        <para>s1kd-validate - Validate an S1000D data module against its schema</para>
      </levelledPara>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>SYNOPSIS</title>
        <para>s1kd-validate [-d &lt;dir&gt;] [-X &lt;URI&gt;] [-vqD] [&lt;datamodules&gt;]</para>
      </levelledPara>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <para>The <emphasis>s1kd-validate</emphasis> tool validates an S1000D data module, checking whether it is a valid XML file and if it is valid against its own S1000D schema.</para>
      </levelledPara>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>OPTIONS</title>
        <para>
          <definitionList>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-d &lt;dir&gt;</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Search for schemas in &lt;dir&gt;. Normally, the URI of the schema is used to fetch it locally or over a network, but this option will force searching to be performed only in the specified directory.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-X &lt;URI&gt;</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Exclude an XML namespace from the validation. Elements in the namespace specified by &lt;URI&gt; are ignored.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-v -q -D</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Set the verbosity of the output, verbose, quiet, and debug. Verbose will explictly indicate success, rather than simply not displaying any errors. Quiet will not output anything.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>&lt;datamodules&gt;</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Any number of data modules to validate.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
          </definitionList>
        </para>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Multi-spec directory with -d option</title>
          <para>The -d option can point either to a directory containing the XSD schema files for a single S1000D spec (i.e. the last part of the schema URI), or to a directory containing schemas for multiple specs. The latter must follow a particular format for the tool to locate the appropriate schemas for a given spec:</para>
          <para>
            <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs23"><![CDATA[schemas/    <-- The directory passed to -d
    S1000D_4-1/
        xml_schema_flat/
            [4.1 XSD files...]
    S1000D_4-2/
        xml_schema_flat/
            [4.2 XSD files...]]]></verbatimText>
          </para>
        </levelledPara>
      </levelledPara>
    </description>
